1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

3
00:00:14,580 --> 00:00:15,720
Who knows.

4
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:22,440
I guess we won't be friends anymore.

5
00:00:35,260 --> 00:00:37,160
Hey, Zen...

6
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:39,740
What is it?

7
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:44,520
Maybe we should just call it off.

8
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:47,000
This competition.

9
00:00:49,280 --> 00:00:50,280
Huh?

10
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:53,400
You're calling it off now, of all times?

11
00:00:55,699 --> 00:00:56,699
I'm kidding.

12
00:00:57,900 --> 00:00:58,480
What?

13
00:00:58,481 --> 00:01:01,040
You take things too seriously.

14
00:01:01,060 --> 00:01:03,500
That's not true... You know that, right?

15
00:01:03,525 --> 00:01:05,005
Backing out means you lose, you know.

16
00:01:05,540 --> 00:01:07,480
This is a contest.

17
00:01:13,180 --> 00:01:14,860
I know.

18
00:02:15,300 --> 00:02:19,800
"Fake Fact Lips"

19
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:25,300
(Episode 5: I Just Don't Get It!)

20
00:02:42,060 --> 00:02:44,279
Good work, Department Head.

21
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,399
This is for you.

22
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,400
Huh?

23
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:49,160
- Thank you, sir.
- It's the first time I've ever won.

24
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:51,920
You know, the slot machine thing
on the vending machine.

25
00:02:52,320 --> 00:02:53,100
Are you sure I can have it?

26
00:02:53,101 --> 00:02:54,499
It's such a special prize.

27
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:56,710
Shido, how many projects
are you on right now?

28
00:02:57,020 --> 00:02:58,020
Uh...

29
00:02:58,045 --> 00:03:00,385
There's Noken Development
and Relto Resource.

30
00:03:00,410 --> 00:03:04,339
And the new affiliate marketing project I just
started researching the day before yesterday.

31
00:03:04,340 --> 00:03:05,940
Wow, that's impressive.

32
00:03:05,965 --> 00:03:07,565
A top employee is really something else.

33
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:10,720
- I'm counting on you.
- Yes, sir.

34
00:03:12,340 --> 00:03:13,860
But don't push yourself too hard.

35
00:03:14,820 --> 00:03:16,230
Thank you, sir.

36
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:35,200
(Yotsuya Ryo: I'm swamped this week. Probably
can't meet. Let's call a truce for now.)

37
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:41,820
Excuse me.

38
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:43,259
Can I help you?

39
00:03:43,260 --> 00:03:44,859
Is Yotsuya in today?

40
00:03:44,860 --> 00:03:46,439
He just left for a team meeting.

41
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:47,400
Oh, I see.

42
00:03:47,401 --> 00:03:49,030
He should be back this evening.

43
00:03:49,130 --> 00:03:50,459
Is it urgent?

44
00:03:50,460 --> 00:03:51,599
Should I give him a message?

45
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:53,150
No, that's okay.

46
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:26,599
(Shido Zen: I left the
T-shirt on your desk.)

47
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,100
(Are you free sometime next week?)

48
00:04:36,900 --> 00:04:38,150
Yotsuya.

49
00:04:39,730 --> 00:04:40,900
Hey.

50
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:45,550
- Um...
- I have a dinner to get to.

51
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:47,800
Let's talk next time.

52
00:04:49,580 --> 00:04:50,640
Oh...

53
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:20,100
(Shido Zen: I left the T-shirt on your
desk. Are you free sometime next week?)

54
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:36,420
Yotsuya...!

55
00:05:36,421 --> 00:05:39,000
- Department Head, good work today.
- Oh.

56
00:05:39,260 --> 00:05:39,980
Um...

57
00:05:39,981 --> 00:05:42,859
There's a planning
meeting in Osaka this Friday.

58
00:05:42,860 --> 00:05:44,679
Oh, right. I haven't given
you the materials yet, have I?

59
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:45,939
Oh, but it's not urgent.

60
00:05:45,940 --> 00:05:46,840
No, I'm afraid I'll forget again.

61
00:05:46,841 --> 00:05:48,016
I'll send them to you right now.

62
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:50,430
- Just a second.
- Sorry to trouble you.

63
00:06:03,410 --> 00:06:05,630
We hope this service will
benefit many more people.

64
00:06:06,450 --> 00:06:08,820
And at the same time, further
grow your company's business.

65
00:06:11,690 --> 00:06:13,010
It's a pleasure working with you.

66
00:06:30,910 --> 00:06:32,149
We'll take care of this.

67
00:06:32,150 --> 00:06:33,390
Oh, thank you.

68
00:06:33,590 --> 00:06:35,810
Wow, the client signed on the spot.

69
00:06:35,890 --> 00:06:37,270
That's Shido-san for you.

70
00:06:37,570 --> 00:06:39,469
That's because we have an excellent team.

71
00:06:39,470 --> 00:06:40,490
You're too modest.

72
00:06:40,510 --> 00:06:42,349
You have an incredible success rate.

73
00:06:42,350 --> 00:06:44,590
The real work starts now.

74
00:06:44,650 --> 00:06:47,130
We need to adjust the
schedule, confirm the budget...

75
00:06:49,350 --> 00:06:51,010
- Shido-san!
- Shido-san?

76
00:06:51,470 --> 00:06:53,990
I'll go get some water!

77
00:07:00,050 --> 00:07:01,850
Sorry, did I scare you?

78
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:03,010
Not at all.

79
00:07:03,035 --> 00:07:04,234
Are you okay?

80
00:07:04,350 --> 00:07:05,710
Yeah, I'm fine.

81
00:07:06,450 --> 00:07:10,190
Lately, just watching you, I can tell
you've been incredibly busy, Shido-san.

82
00:07:11,590 --> 00:07:13,129
Do I look like I'm struggling?

83
00:07:13,310 --> 00:07:14,780
Not struggling, exactly.

84
00:07:15,630 --> 00:07:17,740
But since this week,
you've seemed a bit down.

85
00:07:17,930 --> 00:07:19,810
I even mentioned it to
Department Head Mishima.

86
00:07:21,410 --> 00:07:22,510
How embarrassing.

87
00:07:23,030 --> 00:07:24,249
Making everyone around me worry.

88
00:07:24,250 --> 00:07:27,500
No, no, it's because
we rely on you so much.

89
00:07:29,010 --> 00:07:32,090
At the last dinner party,
didn't Kiritani-san say something too?

90
00:07:33,470 --> 00:07:35,470
She asked if you were getting enough rest.

91
00:07:38,080 --> 00:07:39,350
Getting rest, huh...

92
00:07:43,070 --> 00:07:47,150
In the end, you have to
take care of your own body.

93
00:07:50,750 --> 00:07:52,089
Well, well, Yotsuya-san.

94
00:07:52,090 --> 00:07:54,730
You really are as good
a salesman as they say.

95
00:07:54,830 --> 00:07:55,830
Right?

96
00:07:56,170 --> 00:07:57,870
You're welcome in Osaka anytime.

97
00:07:58,509 --> 00:07:59,805
I'll go talk to HR.

98
00:07:59,830 --> 00:08:02,870
Hey, if you say that, I
might take you seriously.

99
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:06,050
Come on, let's go for a drink.

100
00:08:06,075 --> 00:08:06,745
What do you want to eat?

101
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:07,750
If it's kushikatsu...

102
00:08:07,751 --> 00:08:09,429
- Hey, you.
- Hmm?

103
00:08:09,430 --> 00:08:11,510
We're obviously getting
something with batter first.

104
00:08:12,090 --> 00:08:13,090
No way.

105
00:08:13,270 --> 00:08:14,930
That stuff is a given.

106
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,500
(Incoming call: Yotsuya Ryo)

107
00:08:31,090 --> 00:08:32,090
Huh?

108
00:08:32,150 --> 00:08:33,150
You picked up fast.

109
00:08:34,170 --> 00:08:36,830
- What's up?
- It's nothing, really.

110
00:08:38,030 --> 00:08:40,700
It's just that the project I was busy with
is finally wrapped up.

111
00:08:45,530 --> 00:08:46,530
I'm sorry.

112
00:08:48,010 --> 00:08:49,520
What are you sorry for?

113
00:08:50,390 --> 00:08:51,630
Well...

114
00:08:51,976 --> 00:08:53,736
For not replying to
your messages and stuff.

115
00:08:54,782 --> 00:08:56,762
You mean for deliberately avoiding me?

116
00:08:58,550 --> 00:09:00,089
No, that's not it.

117
00:09:00,090 --> 00:09:02,670
You don't have to call
me for every little thing.

118
00:09:03,049 --> 00:09:04,049
But...

119
00:09:04,870 --> 00:09:07,280
I've been swamped
with my presentation, too.

120
00:09:07,390 --> 00:09:09,560
I haven't had time to think about you.

121
00:09:10,830 --> 00:09:11,830
I see.

122
00:09:13,570 --> 00:09:15,330
Since you said you were busy,

123
00:09:16,670 --> 00:09:19,350
does that mean you're
done with your thing, too?

124
00:09:20,030 --> 00:09:21,030
The presentation is over.

125
00:09:21,510 --> 00:09:22,889
But the real work is just beginning.

126
00:09:22,890 --> 00:09:24,330
Oh, so it went well.

127
00:09:24,750 --> 00:09:27,209
- That's just like you.
- Of course it is.

128
00:09:27,210 --> 00:09:28,680
Don't overdo it.

129
00:09:29,820 --> 00:09:31,170
You haven't collapsed, have you?

130
00:09:32,310 --> 00:09:34,030
As if I'd collapse.

131
00:09:34,530 --> 00:09:36,660
Anyway, how about you?

132
00:09:36,850 --> 00:09:37,850
Me?

133
00:09:38,510 --> 00:09:40,330
Same as always.

134
00:09:40,770 --> 00:09:44,930
But I guess I am a little tired.

135
00:09:47,590 --> 00:09:49,810
So for some reason,

136
00:09:52,490 --> 00:09:56,230
I suddenly wanted to hear your voice.

137
00:09:59,650 --> 00:10:00,650
But...

138
00:10:02,670 --> 00:10:05,030
after hearing your voice,

139
00:10:06,330 --> 00:10:08,170
I guess I really do
want to see you after all.

140
00:10:12,549 --> 00:10:13,549
Yotsuya.

141
00:10:13,990 --> 00:10:16,990
- We've decided on a restaurant.
- I'm on my way.

142
00:10:17,310 --> 00:10:18,310
Ryo.

143
00:10:19,150 --> 00:10:20,569
Where are you right now?

144
00:10:20,570 --> 00:10:21,610
Right now?

145
00:10:21,620 --> 00:10:23,040
In Osaka.

146
00:10:24,210 --> 00:10:25,329
Osaka...?

147
00:10:25,330 --> 00:10:26,330
Yeah.

148
00:10:27,070 --> 00:10:29,020
I'm staying another night.

149
00:10:30,530 --> 00:10:31,670
Sorry, I have to go.

150
00:10:32,330 --> 00:10:34,130
I'll call you when I get back.

151
00:10:40,570 --> 00:10:41,790
Oh, Shido-san, excuse me.

152
00:10:41,830 --> 00:10:42,760
You had a phone call just now.

153
00:10:42,760 --> 00:10:43,760
Oh, sorry.

154
00:10:43,850 --> 00:10:45,010
I'm heading home for the day.

155
00:10:45,650 --> 00:10:46,909
There shouldn't be anything urgent.

156
00:10:46,910 --> 00:10:48,689
Could you tell them I'll
handle it on Monday?

157
00:10:48,690 --> 00:10:49,690
Got it.

158
00:10:51,550 --> 00:10:52,550
It's so far.

159
00:10:53,020 --> 00:10:54,570
Do you have plans?

160
00:10:55,590 --> 00:10:59,000
Nothing much. Just going to unwind a bit.

161
00:11:18,550 --> 00:11:19,720
Ryo.

162
00:11:44,470 --> 00:11:46,540
Because you said you wanted to see me.

163
00:11:54,490 --> 00:11:55,490
What is it?

164
00:11:56,010 --> 00:11:57,146
You could at least look a little happier.

165
00:11:57,170 --> 00:12:02,530
I'm super... happy.

166
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:23,740
You're so cold.

167
00:12:25,040 --> 00:12:28,260
Then you should know what to do, right?

168
00:12:58,700 --> 00:12:59,700
Ryo.

169
00:13:01,500 --> 00:13:02,500
Hmm?

170
00:13:07,490 --> 00:13:08,490
Ryo.

171
00:13:09,940 --> 00:13:12,540
Are you doing all of this just to beat me?

172
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:19,130
That's...

173
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:23,580
Zen, aren't you doing the same thing?

174
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:28,100
I...

175
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:32,280
Zen.

176
00:13:36,140 --> 00:13:37,830
Why are you crying...?

177
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:39,830
I'm not crying.

178
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,490
Ryo...

179
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:50,940
For the sake of winning,
would you do this with anyone?

180
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:53,080
Huh...?

181
00:13:54,820 --> 00:13:56,450
Do you want to beat me that badly?

182
00:13:57,333 --> 00:13:59,583
- That's not it.
- Then what is it?

183
00:14:01,060 --> 00:14:02,250
Why are we...

184
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:06,230
doing this?

185
00:14:23,420 --> 00:14:24,880
The truth is...

186
00:14:28,159 --> 00:14:31,129
from the very beginning, I never
cared about the competition.

187
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:39,080
I just...

188
00:14:41,740 --> 00:14:43,880
wanted to be with you.

189
00:14:46,540 --> 00:14:48,650
I've liked you for a long time.

190
00:14:50,560 --> 00:14:53,140
Ever since high school...

191
00:14:55,820 --> 00:14:56,930
Huh?

192
00:14:57,380 --> 00:14:58,640
So I...

193
00:15:01,420 --> 00:15:04,580
wasn't hitting on
you for the competition.

194
00:15:06,220 --> 00:15:08,740
I genuinely wanted you.

195
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:21,520
I'm sorry for doing something
that felt like I was tricking you.

196
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:25,850
From the start,
I was destined to lose this competition...

197
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:29,700
Zen...

198
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:32,610
If that's the case,

199
00:15:33,930 --> 00:15:35,950
then be my boyfriend.

200
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:38,640
Huh...?

201
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:45,790
You pursued me and won.
Now you have to see it through.

202
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:50,359
What do you mean, 'won me over'?

203
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:56,370
The winner's word is law, right?

204
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,940
Aren't you going to say anything?

205
00:16:08,710 --> 00:16:09,790
Sorry...

206
00:16:12,120 --> 00:16:13,530
I'm just so confused.

207
00:16:14,550 --> 00:16:15,550
Confused about what?

208
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:20,840
No.

209
00:16:21,540 --> 00:16:26,420
We talked about this before, didn't we?

210
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:30,500
About winning or losing this competition.

211
00:16:31,540 --> 00:16:33,836
You mean that time you said you were
quitting the competition out of the blue?

212
00:16:33,860 --> 00:16:35,200
I already apologized for that.

213
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:38,830
You said back then...

214
00:16:40,360 --> 00:16:43,750
That we might not be able
to be friends anymore, right?

215
00:16:46,210 --> 00:16:47,210
Huh?

216
00:16:48,170 --> 00:16:50,610
That's because we'd be lovers, obviously.

217
00:16:55,820 --> 00:16:57,650
Why'd you have to say it like that?

218
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:58,760
Huh?

219
00:17:00,080 --> 00:17:04,580
Do you have any idea
how long I've been agonizing over that?

220
00:17:04,850 --> 00:17:07,220
You took it literally?

221
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:10,650
How dense can you be?

222
00:17:10,690 --> 00:17:13,210
If it meant I couldn't
be with you anymore...

223
00:17:15,113 --> 00:17:20,113
I would've rather we just stayed friends.

224
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:26,410
I thought I'd done something irreversible.

225
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:28,460
I regretted it so much.

226
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:35,360
If you didn't fall for me, I...

227
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:42,280
would lose you.

228
00:17:44,020 --> 00:17:45,020
Ryo...

229
00:17:47,740 --> 00:17:49,080
That's why...

230
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:55,730
If you wanted to date me,
you should've just lost sooner.

231
00:17:55,950 --> 00:17:57,619
Says the one who was
into me from the start.

232
00:17:57,620 --> 00:17:58,779
You've got some nerve.

233
00:17:58,780 --> 00:17:59,859
Sore loser.

234
00:17:59,860 --> 00:18:00,860
Takes one to know one.

235
00:18:02,020 --> 00:18:04,440
By the way, don't get the wrong idea.

236
00:18:04,740 --> 00:18:08,750
I only went easy on you
because you were trying so hard.

237
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:15,300
You just can't be honest, can you?

238
00:18:20,730 --> 00:18:25,980
But that's what I like about you.

239
00:18:27,850 --> 00:18:31,650
It's really throwing me off
when you're suddenly so direct.

240
00:18:33,730 --> 00:18:34,900
Even so...

241
00:18:37,490 --> 00:18:41,760
I don't want us to miss our chance again
because I didn't tell you how I feel.

242
00:18:43,970 --> 00:18:45,070
Like idiots.

243
00:18:46,170 --> 00:18:48,570
Getting so serious over
such a stupid competition.

244
00:18:49,630 --> 00:18:51,000
Both of us.

245
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:58,360
Anyone would turn into an idiot
in front of the person they like...

246
00:19:02,470 --> 00:19:03,490
Zen.

247
00:19:07,250 --> 00:19:08,540
I like you.

248
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:13,480
Me too.

249
00:19:15,690 --> 00:19:16,690
I only want Ryo.

250
00:19:18,323 --> 00:19:19,323
It has to be Ryo.

251
00:19:21,110 --> 00:19:22,320
Sorry.

252
00:19:23,030 --> 00:19:27,410
I can't hold back anymore.

253
00:19:44,410 --> 00:19:49,850
See? Now you really
can't live without me.

254
00:19:52,710 --> 00:19:54,190
No.

255
00:19:55,290 --> 00:19:56,860
I already...

256
00:19:58,670 --> 00:20:00,240
couldn't live without you, Zen.

257
00:21:24,690 --> 00:21:27,910
Being with you is driving me crazy.

258
00:21:29,310 --> 00:21:33,540
I'll take that as a compliment.

259
00:21:34,290 --> 00:21:35,800
Whatever.

260
00:21:38,923 --> 00:21:39,923
Zen.

261
00:21:43,290 --> 00:21:45,320
Only look at me.

262
00:22:35,630 --> 00:22:37,190
Hey, Zen.

263
00:22:41,290 --> 00:22:42,460
After the exams are over...

264
00:22:43,270 --> 00:22:44,500
let's go somewhere.

265
00:22:45,190 --> 00:22:46,550
We're studying for entrance exams.

266
00:22:48,070 --> 00:22:50,370
If we go out and have
fun after just one test...

267
00:22:51,700 --> 00:22:53,220
I'll never catch up to my brother.

268
00:22:55,510 --> 00:22:57,180
I wish I could grow up faster.

269
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:00,830
What a childish thing to say.

270
00:23:01,330 --> 00:23:04,880
When we're adults, we can go far away.

271
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:08,570
And be with the person we love.

272
00:23:18,470 --> 00:23:19,770
I should get some rest too.

273
00:24:27,190 --> 00:24:32,760
You told Yotsuya-san something like,
'You're welcome in Osaka anytime, ' right?

274
00:24:33,183 --> 00:24:35,543
Of course. That was
just to set up the surprise.

275
00:24:36,510 --> 00:24:37,779
So, Futami-san...

276
00:24:37,780 --> 00:24:40,140
Are you really planning to go
without telling him anything?

277
00:24:40,750 --> 00:24:44,620
A rival's entrance is always sudden.

278
00:24:46,510 --> 00:24:48,650
As the ace of the Osaka branch...

279
00:24:49,196 --> 00:24:51,756
I'm going to make my mark.

280
00:25:55,470 --> 00:25:57,446
(Next Episode)
How much further do you want me to go?

281
00:25:57,470 --> 00:25:58,799
(Episode 6: There's no need for the word 'Tentatively')
Are you going on a date?

282
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:00,109
Yotsuya-san?

283
00:26:00,110 --> 00:26:02,530
Stop kidding around. Give it back.

284
00:26:03,890 --> 00:26:04,929
Seriously?

285
00:26:04,930 --> 00:26:07,400
I've been in love with you since college.

286
00:26:08,110 --> 00:26:11,979
Getting first place once has
really gone to your head, hasn't it?

287
00:26:11,980 --> 00:26:13,030
Right. I don't want it.

288
00:26:14,430 --> 00:26:15,110
Huh?

289
00:26:15,210 --> 00:26:18,249
You two are a classic
case of mutual admiration.

290
00:26:18,250 --> 00:26:20,230
You should be careful too, Shido-san.

291
00:26:20,410 --> 00:26:22,330
The time you have to
see each other is precious.

